</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[712,791,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1986,2010]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,833,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-145@5.[151,1435,833,1962]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypatoma loxosaris, male genitalia (gen. slide 195/19, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690579/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) do not match those of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1825" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[1161,1432,330,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Hypatima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1161,1271,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Hypatima</emphasis>
Hübner, 1825
</taxonomicName>
. The generic assignment of the species needs to be appraised in the context of a revision.
</paragraph>
